main event: Several bright orange lights or fireballs were observed moving at high speeds in the sky near Orlando, Florida on January 7, 1962.
interesting points: The lights appeared to move in a south to north direction at fairly high speed.
The lights were round or oval in shape, very bright orange in color, and moved in pairs or groups of 3-5.
The witness could not identify the lights as flares or aircraft.
An investigator's note indicates the lights were likely a cluster of burning or chemically-ignited balloons, but there was insufficient data for a definite determination.
A separate report describes a chandelier-like object and intermittent light that were further investigated.
sighted object: Bright orange lights or fireballs in the sky
